cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with using 3D information in convolutional neural networks for recognition tasks, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also focuses on indoor and outdoor 3D semantic segmentation datasets, which suggests robotics (cs.RO) as another likely sub-category. The proposed method involves a new data-driven depth discretization scheme, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with optimizing memory usage in 3D convolution, which could also be relevant to graphics (cs.GR).
